HALİT TAŞDEMİR IE 360 HW 1 2022-04-13 1-INTRODUCTION

I wanted to see the effect of USD/TRY exchange rates on cost of living indices for wage earners for clothing (ICC 1995=100), consumer price index for clothing, and overall google search for “Giyim”. I wanted to question how the increase in USD/TRY exchange rates affected customers’ access to clothes and how much these datas are correlated.

CPI

GOOGLE SEARCH OF “giyim”

plot(1:150, giyimgoogle[,1], type="l", xlab="months", ylab="search of 'giyim'")

CORRELATION MATRIX

data <- data.frame( hw_data[,2],  hw_data[,3], hw_data[,4], giyimgoogle)
names(data) <- c("USD/TRY", "Cost of Living for Clothing Expenses", "CPI for clothing" , "Google Cloth Search")
data_correlation = cor(data)
corrplot(data_correlation, method="number")

CONCLUSION

I wanted to learn how USD/TRY rates going up affected the clothing sector. At first I plotted the graphs and the correlation could be easily seen by simply looking. After that, I decided to make a correlation matrix. As can be seen in the correlation matrix, USD/TRY, Cost of living for clothing and CPI are highly correlated, whereas people’s search of “giyim” also decreased since it gets harder to afford clothes.
